DuDe!... DUDE!...DudE!...dUdE!...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujammermon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jammermon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/27/01 10:42:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Item spec bonuses past Level &amp; realm point rewards</span><hr size=1> No Item up will give you use of Poisons/Spells/Styles over your train level. <br>
<br>
Item ups will let you be more EFFECTIVE at using the skill. IE If you get a Pierce +2 with skill 22 you will then Pierce as IF you trained to 24. But a Pierce 24 style will not be available to you. <br>
<br>
Realm Points do add to actual use. Skill 22 + 2 Realm Points means you could use style 24.<br>
<br>
Whisper<br>
